ack...\n\nActually, looking at the error again - it seems like apiKey is a protected path. This makes sense for security reasons - the system doesn't want people accidentally committing API keys. \n\nThe schema indicates that apiKey accepts either a plain string or a SecretRef object, which is the proper way to reference credentials without hardcoding them. I should use the SecretRef format to point to the API key stored in an environment variable or external file instead of embedding it directly.","thinkingSignature":"70ab4eeaabc6f88c8f3cef9177eccebffef08b61d3f7e4046099fc789fb83ca9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_klih2uud85ni_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get","path":"models.providers"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":444,"output":527,"cacheRead":54912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55883,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779335387423,"responseId":"065db3db6eed2f92e8343ed77ed246ee"}}
