{"type":"message","id":"31a24e0e","parentId":"1f9ec842","timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:39:53.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config looks correct. The openrouter provider has deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free added. But the model reference might need to be just \"openrouter/deepseek-v4-flash\" without the \"deepseek/\" prefix since it's already under the openrouter provider.\n\nActually, looking at how other providers work in OpenClaw - for example minimax uses \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\" where \"minimax\" is the provider ID and \"MiniMax-M2.7\" is the model ID within that provider.\n\nSo for openrouter, it should be \"openrouter/<model-id>\" where the model-id is the full OpenRouter model ID including the provider prefix like \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\".\n\nBut that would result in \"openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\" which has two slashes and a colon. That might be causing issues.\n\nActually wait - looking at the OpenRouter API, the model ID \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\" already includes the provider prefix \"deepseek/\". So when I reference it in OpenClaw, I should use just the part after the provider prefix, OR I should use the full ID as-is.\n\nLet me think about this differently. In OpenClaw's model reference system:\n- Provider: openrouter\n- Model ID within provider: deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free (the full OpenRouter model ID)\n\nSo the reference would be \"openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\" - which has the provider \"openrouter\" and the model ID \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\".\n\nBut this is confusing because the model ID already has a slash in it. \n\nThe double slash pattern \"openrouter/deepseek/...\" is actually valid in OpenClaw's model reference format. OpenRouter's API accepts model IDs like \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\" as-is, so this shouldn't be the problem. The error about the model not being allowed suggests something else is preventing access - possibly the model ID format or a restriction on free-tier models.","thinkingSignature":"5804ff67716bde4c9266529607ef053413ffe7ad109e608495cf3012e7445815"},{"type":"text","text":"配置看起来正确。让我直接测试 OpenRouter API 是否能正常调用这个模型：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y4c2emo8tw1v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST \"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer sk-or-…75c4\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free\",\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Hi, reply with just OK\"}],\"max_tokens\":10}' 2>/dev/null | head -c 500"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22323,"output":632,"cacheRead":46051,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69006,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779338382847,"responseId":"065dbf8fa9918568e440dd1d2b9e04d2"}}
